[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["NZ default banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Pirongia"]}," is a little village about 30 minutes drive south of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hamilton (New Zealand)"],["Hamilton"]]},", in southern ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Waikato"]]},", in the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["North Island"]]}," of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["New Zealand"]]},". It is located at the base of Mount Pirongia. There is a little info centre in town that will give you hiking info and where to go.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\nPirongia is about 30 km south of Hamilton and 12 km west of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Te Awamutu"]]},", off State Highway 3 as it runs south from Hamilton to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Otorohanga"]]},". For a more direct trip, get off the highways and take the country roads through ",{"type":"''","value":["Temple View"]}," and see the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Mormon Temple"]}," in this area.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"'''","value":["Mormon Temple"]}," at Ngahinapouri."]},{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"'''","value":["Pirongia Forest Park"]},". There is some great hiking on Mt Pirongia. "]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\nThere is a pub that serves food and a couple of cafes.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["isPartOf"],["Waikato"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wikipedia:Pirongia"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Dmoz:Regional\/Oceania\/New_Zealand\/Waikato\/Localities\/Pirongia\/"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["outlinecity"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["geo"],["-38"],["175.2"]]}]